    "intro": "Interpretation asks what John intends his reader to *understand* from this chapter — situated against the Gospel's prologue (1:1-18), its purpose statement (20:30-31), and the first-century reality of Samaritan-Jewish hostility. The five movements below trace the argument from divine appointment through universal confession.",
